Exec Connect Call - July 16, 2024

Presentation Deck

Accenture wants and needs to channelize the passion and momentum internally to effectively drive intentional participation and engagement within the GSF

Engagement with the GSF = positive perception within Accenture and in industry

Notes

Pain Points
  • At the individual level, there has been a push for AI and near-revenue projects and initiatives. GS/Sustainability = everyone has to do it on their 20% time or on their own time
  • Don't have budget for people to work on green software. Only Thomas gets paid to work on green software.

Need to explore broader questions:

  • How does GSF tie into Microsoft products? Cloud for Sustainability, Azure Cloud for Optimization
  • Microsoft wants to keep "good face" given the impacts reported given their acceleration in AI

Thomas putting together a 'Green Plan’

Tammy mentioned she would love to create SC use cases with customers but she doesn't have time

Her boss said: what if we take you out of your job for 30 days to focus on these use cases?

  • Tammy thinking around Kubernetes - how can we measure each pre-cut templates and what actions can we take to make them more efficient, and how do we measure the workloads working on top of that efficient?

Notes

  • The digitalization story for Siemens is Siemens is an accelerator
  • A big topic of conversation: operational requirements for sustainable practices
  • Runs internal hackathons

  • Looking for an executive brief they can share with the CEO executive staff that includes:

    • Capabilities
    • Responsibilities/ priorities
    • Tools that drive product solutions
  • Incredibly interested in the Policy Radar project. Looking for guidance: here's what the new regulations are and what you are going to be accountable for by X date (clarify when reporting will be recommended versus required and to what level)

  • Expressed the benefit of getting the following insights from the GSF:

    • Analyst reaction of how regulators are going to evaluate measurement and reporting
    • How deep into your supply chain do you have to go to have auditable reporting
    • How do we convince companies to do better reporting? How do we get their declaration to do better?

  • They have a European user group

    • Suzanne going to present on digital sustainability
    • 1500 people who interact throughout the year
    • have a conference each year

  1. Every quarter, Siemens has a big results presentation - what progress/contributions does Carolin want to share at the next meeting?
  2. How can we make green software a focus for an upcoming hackathon, and how can GSF play a greater role?
  3. How is Siemens thinking about AI and who's being tasked with ensuring its sustainability?
